  "bulletins": [
    {
      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "Avalanches can in many places be released in the old snowpack. Mostly these are medium-sized and can be released even by a single winter sport participant. Caution is to be exercised in particular on west, north and east facing slopes above approximately 1800 m. Remotely triggered avalanches are possible. <br/> <br/> The avalanche prone locations are prevalent and are barely recognisable. Whumpfing sounds and the formation of shooting cracks when stepping on the snowpack are a clear indication of a weakly bonded snowpack. <br/> <br/> Mostly small loose snow avalanches are possible as a consequence of warming during the day and solar radiation.",
        "highlights": "The conditions are precarious."
      },
